narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned more in-depth knowledge about the mechanics of camera and lighting, as well as art/conceptual knowledge and insight via crits.
I used to consider photography to be a hobby. This class drove to take photography more seriously and began to develop my unique understanding of photography.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course is generally very well structured, altho I do wish there were more hands-on workshops (lighting, flash, pushing/pulling).
Its a small size class. Everyone is familiar with each other and knows others work. The communication is deep and inspiring.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would definitely recommend this course to another student -learning to develop my visual voice in a systematic manner helped me grow so much as an artist. The lively atmosphere and intimate discussions of the classroom had always made my day.
Yes. Photography will benefits students majoring in architecture.
